transformations.description: This source is a custom query using a union. The first portion of the query will use the customer_stg,policy_risk_key_reference,basicpolicy_stg and policy_stg tables. The second portion of the query will use the customer_stg,policy_risk_key_reference,basicpolicyapp_stg and application_stg tables.
transformations.name: src_query

object.customQuery:
select
	distinct
    prkr.policy_system_id as policy_risk_key_reference_system_id,
	prkr.policy_number as policy_number,
	prkr.policy_module_number as policy_module_number,
	prkr.policy_key as policy_key,
	prkr.line_system_id as line_system_id,
	prkr.line_of_business as line_of_business,
	bp.statuscd,
	bp.expirationdt,
	c.system_id as system_id,
	c.index_name as index_name,
	c.customer_number as customer_number,
	c.status as status,
	p.systemid as policy_system_id,
	p.customerref as policy_customer_number,
	p.accountref as policy_account_number,
	a.systemid as application_system_id,
	cast(a.applicationnumber as VARCHAR(255)) as application_number,-- Cast to VARCHAR to match  data type
	a.customerref as application_customer_number,
	tgt.uw_dashboard_customer_details_row_id as tgt_customer_details_row_id,
	tgt.uw_dashboard_customer_details_md5_hash_value as tgt_customer_details_md5_hash_value
from
	dbo.customer_stg c
left join dbo.policy_stg p
    on c.system_id = p.customerref
left join dbo.policy_risk_key_reference prkr
    on p.systemid = prkr.policy_system_id
    and p.cmmcontainer = prkr.policy_cmm_container
left join dbo.basicpolicy_stg bp
    on prkr.policy_system_id = bp.systemid
    and prkr.policy_cmm_container = bp.cmmcontainer
left join dbo.application_stg a
    on p.systemid = a.policyref
left join dbo.uw_dashboard_customer_details tgt
    on prkr.line_system_id = tgt.line_system_id
    and c.system_id = tgt.customer_system_id
    --and prkr.policy_key = tgt.policy_key
where
	prkr.policy_risk_key_reference_row_effective_end_date = '9999-12-31'  
--and
--prkr.policy_key= 'HP13234264003'
union
select
	distinct
    prkr.policy_system_id as policy_risk_key_reference_system_id,
	prkr.policy_number as policy_number,
	prkr.policy_module_number as policy_module_number,
	prkr.policy_key as policy_key,
	prkr.line_system_id as line_system_id,
	prkr.line_of_business as line_of_business,
	bp.statuscd,
	bp.expirationdt,
	c.system_id as system_id,
	c.index_name as index_name,
	c.customer_number as customer_number,
	c.status as status,
	p.systemid as policy_system_id,
	p.customerref as policy_customer_number,
	p.accountref as policy_account_number,
	a.systemid as application_system_id,
	cast(a.applicationnumber as VARCHAR(255)) as application_number,-- Cast to VARCHAR to match  data type
	a.customerref as application_customer_number,
	tgt.uw_dashboard_customer_details_row_id as tgt_customer_details_row_id,
	tgt.uw_dashboard_customer_details_md5_hash_value as tgt_customer_details_md5_hash_value
from
	dbo.customer_stg c
left join dbo.application_stg a
    on
	a.customerref = c.system_id
left join dbo.policy_risk_key_reference prkr
    on
	a.systemid = prkr.policy_system_id
	and a.cmmcontainer = prkr.policy_cmm_container
left join dbo.basicpolicyapp_stg bp
    on
	prkr.policy_system_id = bp.systemid
	and prkr.policy_cmm_container = bp.cmmcontainer
left join dbo.policy_stg p
    on p.systemid = a.policyref
left join dbo.uw_dashboard_customer_details tgt
    on prkr.line_system_id = tgt.line_system_id
    and c.system_id = tgt.customer_system_id
    --and prkr.policy_key = tgt.policy_key
where
	prkr.policy_risk_key_reference_row_effective_end_date = '9999-12-31'  
--and
--prkr.policy_key= 'HP13234264003';

transformations.description: This expression will implement logic for the following fields - policy_status_description,policy_customer_number and application_customer_number. We will also create the hash key value for comparing data to the target.
transformations.name: exp_uw_dashboard_customer_details

fields.name: md5_hash_value
fields.expression:
ltrim(rtrim(MD5('policy_risk_key_reference_system_id' || TO_CHAR(policy_risk_key_reference_system_id ||
'policy_number' || policy_number ||
'policy_module_number' || policy_module_number ||
'policy_key' || policy_key ||
'line_system_id' || TO_CHAR(line_system_id) ||
'line_of_business' || line_of_business ||
'statuscd' || statuscd ||
'expirationdt' || TO_CHAR(expirationdt,'YYY-MM-DD') ||
'system_id' || TO_CHAR(system_id) ||
'index_name' || index_name ||
'customer_number' || TO_CHAR(customer_number) ||
'status' || status ||
'policy_system_id' || TO_CHAR(policy_system_id) ||
'policy_customer_number' || TO_CHAR(policy_customer_number) ||
'policy_account_number' || TO_CHAR(policy_account_number) ||
'application_system_id' || TO_CHAR(application_system_id) ||
'application_number' || application_number ||
'application_customer_number' || TO_CHAR(application_customer_number)
))))

fields.name: o_policy_status_description
fields.expression:
IIF(statuscd = 'Non-Renewed' AND expirationdt >= SYSDATE, 
    'Nonrenewed (inforce)', 
IIF(statuscd = 'Non-Renewed' AND expirationdt < SYSDATE, 
        'Nonrenewed (expired)', 
        statuscd))
